The article is a statement by the President on the anniversary of the attack on the U.S. Marine Barracks in Beirut, Lebanon. The President remembers the 241 American Marines, soldiers, and sailors who lost their lives in the terrorist attack and pays tribute to their courage and sacrifice. The military personnel were in Beirut to bring peace and stability to Lebanon. The President also honors the brave service of all members of the U.S. military and international peacekeepers who are protecting Americans and promoting freedom and security. The President expresses hope for a new government in Lebanon that actively promotes stability in the region and prosperity for its people.